From Carl Ellison Subject Re text of White House announcement and Q As on clipper chip encryption In article rwing UUCP pat rwing UUCP Pat Myrto writes For example, a conversation between a suspect and a lawyer will no longer be private from Big Brother eavesdropping Now, almost years later, we have the right words for the problem here Phone calls are virtual visits Those experienced in virtual reality would know from that title that phone calls need to have all the properties of a walk in the park with your friend security from casual overhearing and easy verification to see if anyone is listening secretively As designed, they fail at that trouble is, telephones were invented a long time ago and people didn't realize the danger or the concept of virtual reality back then Disclaimer All opinions expressed are my own, of course Carl Ellison Stratus Computer Inc M BKW TEL Fairbanks Boulevard Marlborough MA FAX